ch.codebulb.lambdaomega

Class C<T,K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions.OmegaObject
      • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.C<T,K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of an entry when accessed sequentially
    K - the type of a key for indexed access
    V - the type of a value for indexed access
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    I<K,V>, ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>, StreamableI
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    L, M

    public abstract class C<T,K,V>
extends OmegaObject
implements StreamableI, ReadonlyIndexedI<K,V>
    The "C" stands for "common collection". This is the base class of all LambdaOmega collections which implements common functionality.

    It also provides common static helper methods for collections.
